# Jenkins tools configuration guide

a\)

**ssh to Jenkins VM and run below to install required packages **

sudo yum install git

sudo yum install java-devel

**b\) sonar scanner**

Login to Jenkins and go to

Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Plugins

![](data:image/*;base64,)

Click on 'Available' Tab and search for sonarqube

![](data:image/*;base64,)

Go to :- Jenkins &gt;&gt; Global Tool Configuration

and set the config for sonar scanner as shown below:-

![](data:image/*;base64,)

**SonarQube Server Config**

Go to :- Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Jenkins &gt;&gt; Configure System

nd set 'SonarQube servers' as shown below

![](data:image/*;base64,)

**c\) Maven**

Login to Jenkins and go to

Jenkins &gt;&gt; Global Tool Configuration

Set Maven tool configuration

![](data:image/*;base64,)

d\) Ansible

Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Plugins

Search for[Ansible plugin](https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Ansible+Plugin)and install it

e\)

Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Plugins

Search for[Build Pipeline Plugin](https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Ansible+Plugin)and install it

[      
](https://plugins.jenkins.io/build-pipeline-plugin)f\)

Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Jenkins &gt;&gt; Manage Plugins

Search for[Parameterized Trigger plugin](https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Ansible+Plugin)and install it

g\)

\#Create a settings.xml file for nexus upload credentials

sudo mkdir /opt/jenkins\_settings

sudo chmod 755 /opt/jenkins\_settings

sudo chown ec2-user -R /opt/jenkins\_settings

copy [java-devops/jenkins/config/settings.xml](/java-devops/jenkins/config/settings.xml)  to /opt/jenkins\_settings
